Subject: Re: [VB] Problem in the head (valves)???

John,
This could be a dropped valve seat. I would remove the rocker arm assembly from the head, then take a straight edge and place it along the top of all four valves. See if the any of the valve stems are higher than the others.
Dave

> I went to adjust the valves on my 1600 DP in my 71 Westy and found that the #1 
> valves would not adjust. No matter how far I backed them out, I could not get 
> even the thinnest feeler gauge in there. Did a compression check and I got ZERO 
> compression on #1 but very good compression on #2 (140 psi). The starnge thing 
> is that I have noticed no loss in power or performance?!?!? 
> Soooooo, I am assuming that it is a valve issue on #1, sound right?? Is there 
> anything else that would cause this?? Other possibilities? I have a replacement 
> head to put on, but if there are other possible culprits, I'd like to know about 
> them before wasting my time with installing the new head. 
